  "doc_id": "51078",
  "text": "For static indoor measurements, the measured CIR is essentially only one snapshot of an environment, i.e. only one temporal observation is available. The spatial method discussed in [CITATION_1] , e.g. the classical beamforming and high resolution algorithms like MUSIC cannot be directly applied, since the covariance matrix of the array outputs would be rank-deficient due to the limited temporal samples. Different algorithms were proposed to address this issue, e.g. a spatial smoothing technique in [CITATION_2] and an iterative 2D Unitary ESPRIT method in [CITATION_3] for virtual planar arrays. In this paper, we are interested in both delay and angle information of the multipath components. For the sake of simplicity, a conventional frequency beamforming algorithm is used [CITATION_4] . Note that frequency beamforming algorithms were only used to estimate the angle and delay of the direct path between the transmitter (Tx) and receiver (Rx) for indoor ranging and localization purpose in [CITATION_5] .",
